label: ZMNHWD
info_overview:
Qubino Flush RGBW module controls RGB/RGBW strips and LED strips or bulbs and has 5 special scene effects. It can also control halogen lights and fans. Its extremely small size allows for easy installation behind wall sockets and switches. Controlled devices may be powered by 12 or 24 VDC.

Supported control types:

  • Push button (monostable switch)
  • Bistable switch

This should hopefully work with models ZMNHWD1-ZMNHWD8 (which work on different frequencies).
info_inclusion:
To include the device, press the service button 3 times within 2 seconds. The LED will turn green if the device was properly included.

The device supports auto inclusion: Install the device and connect the power. The auto inclusion function will be active for about 2 minutes.
info_exclusion: To exclude the device, press the service button 3 times within 2 seconds. The green LED will blink if the device was properly included and the device will be reset to factory defaults.

options.label: Romantic

options.label: Party scene
options.overview: random flashing between colours

parameters.label: Auto Scene Mode
parameters.overview:
• 1-127 – delay duration is 1 sec to 127 sec 
  • 1001-1127 – delay duration is from 1 min to 127 min. This parameter has no effect on Lighting and Party Scene.

parameters.label: Memorize device status at power cut
parameters.description: Device will be set to status memorized before power cut.

options.label: Do not memorize
options.overview: device does not memorize its status at power cut. Load is disconnected

options.label: Memorize
options.overview: device memorizes its status at the power cut. Load will be set to the status from before power cut

• 0 – Auto OFF disabled 
  • 1 – 32536 = 1 second – 32536 seconds Auto OFF

parameters.overview:
• 0 – Auto ON disabled
  • 1 – 32536 = 1 second – 32536 seconds Auto ON

1 – 127 = from 1 to 127 seconds

associations.label: Send basic report to this group
associations.overview:
The Module can be set 1 auto-report ID in Group 1.

The Module will send BASIC_REPORT to device associated in Group 1 when correspond Device is activated.

commandclass.name: NO_OPERATION
commandclass.label: No Operation - used for PINGing a device.

channels.name: config_decimal
channels.label: Scene
channels.overview: Select one of 6 pre-defined scenes; 1 – Ocean (soft flowing between shades of blue color) 2 – Lightning (fast flashing of white color) 3 – Rainbow (flowing between colors of rainbow) 4 – Snow (flowing between shades of white and cyan color) 5 – Romantic (soft flowing of the red color) 6 – Party scene (random flashing between colors)

channels.name: config_decimal
channels.label: Scene Color Change Duration
channels.overview: Duration between color change in scenes. Has no effect on Lighting and Party Scene. 1-127 – delay duration is 1 sec to 127 sec 1001-1127 – delay duration is from 1 min to 127 min.
